                        <p class="card-text">Hello fellow students! With finals week approaching, I thought it would be helpful to share some tips that have worked well for me in the past. Here are my top 5 strategies for acing your exams:</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>Start early:</strong> Begin your revision at least two weeks before the exam date. This gives you time to cover all topics and reduces last-minute stress.</li>
                            <li><strong>Create a study schedule:</strong> Allocate specific time slots for each subject, ensuring you cover all areas evenly.</li>
                            <li><strong>Use active recall:</strong> Instead of just re-reading notes, try to recall information from memory. This helps reinforce your learning.</li>
                            <li><strong>Take regular breaks:</strong> Use the Pomodoro technique - study for 25 minutes, then take a 5-minute break. This helps maintain focus and prevents burnout.</li>
                            <li><strong>Practice past papers:</strong> This familiarizes you with the exam format and types of questions you might encounter.</li>
                        </ol>
                        <p>Remember, everyone has different study methods that work for them. These are just suggestions based on my experience. What strategies have worked well for you?</p>
